# BhuMap — memory and skills (Cursor)

## Skills (project, for Cursor Agent Skills)

- Location: `.cursor/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`
- Reference docs: `.cursor/skills/<skill-name>/references/*.md`
- These mirror `.claude/skills/`. If you edit one tree, sync to the other (see `AGENTS.md`).

Available skills: `caveman`, `domain-logic`, `emi-and-payments`, `maps-and-plots`, `roles-and-access`, `supabase-architecture`, `ui-patterns`.

When a topic matches a skill’s description, **read** that `SKILL.md` and follow it; open `references/*` as needed.

## Structured memory (canonical)

- Index: `.claude/memory/CLAUDE.md` (table of what each file is for)
- Paths below are repo-root relative:

| File | Load when |
|------|-----------|
| `.claude/memory/domain-model.md` | Schema, entities, relationships |
| `.claude/memory/schema.md` | SQL tables/columns |
| `.claude/memory/business-rules/plot-rules.md` | Plots, map |
| `.claude/memory/business-rules/sale-rules.md` | Sales flow |
| `.claude/memory/business-rules/emi-rules.md` | EMI, payments, cron |
| `.claude/memory/business-rules/commission-rules.md` | Agent commission |
| `.claude/memory/business-rules/lead-rules.md` | Leads (phase 2) |
| `.claude/memory/decisions.md` | Past architectural decisions |
| `.claude/memory/open-questions.md` | Unresolved domain questions |

**Do not** invent domain rules when these files exist — **read** the relevant file(s) first.

## Ground rule

Discuss domain + data model before writing code; RLS is the access boundary (see root `CLAUDE.md`).
